{
  "stem": "13213.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then, this was the end of just about the spring of 1943 or beginning of spring 1943, the Ukrainian bandits have organized an army of about maybe, I don't know, 8,000, 10,000 soldiers or bandits with arms, and attacked the town of Huta Stepanska in order to liquidate the Polish enclave and kill them all.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they did it before in some other small villages-- killed all the Polacks.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the Polacks-- the Polish people started to run away, to a town by the name of Rafalowka, which was called [?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Nova ?] Rafalowka.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They were all running away to the town of Rafalowka.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And from there, they were going-- the Germans would take the young ones on the trains and ship them to Germany to work for them.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We decided to go with the Polish people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we came into the town of Rafalowka.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We found some people that gave us some food.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we found some Jews in there that escaped.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And there was a lady that was in Huta Stepanska, a young girl that came with us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "She was all alone, so she attached herself to us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And she was with us in Rafalowka.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "In there, we went to the station where they were recruiting people, young people, to go to work in Germany.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We were in the lineup.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And as the people were coming out from the checkup and registration, we asked if they-- how do they check.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And they said they undress everybody, presumably checking if somebody was Jewish, so they could check.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Well, in that case, we decided we cannot go to Germany because they would undress us and find out we're Jews and we're finished.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
